</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F16A36B5FFC2622DFF2DA2C3FE8EFC7E" blockId="2.[151,1362,812,1185]" box="[159,297,992,1015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Podobranchs</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F16A36B5FFC2622DFF2DA529FD13FBA8" blockId="2.[151,1362,812,1185]" box="[159,692,1034,1057]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Lobe-shaped epipods + +</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F16A36B5FFC2622DFF2DA516FC85FB28" blockId="2.[151,1362,812,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Strap-like epipods (mastigobranchs) + + + + + Setal epipods (setobranchs) + + + + + Exopods + + +</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F16A36B5FFC2622DFF74A5FBFBEEFA7E" blockId="2.[151,1437,1240,1900]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="95444B44FFC2622DFED8A5FBFD32FB7B" author="Banner" box="[362,661,1240,1266]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" refString="Banner, A. H. &amp; Banner, D. M. (1983) An annotated checklist of the alpheid shrimp from the western Indian Ocean. Travaux et Documents de l'ORSTOM, 158, 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="1983">
Banner &amp; Banner (
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFDFFA5FBFD2BFB7B" box="[589,652,1240,1266]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1983.0">1983</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the presence of spiniform setae on the ischium and merus of the third and fifth pereiopods (
<collectionCode id="97C4AE70FFC2622DFE63A5DEFE44FA9E" box="[465,483,1277,1303]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">P</collectionCode>
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFE50A5DEFDA8FA9E" box="[482,527,1277,1303]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
) is a variable character. Indeed, 
<bibRefCitation id="95444B44FFC2622DFC3BA5DEFB0AFA9E" author="Banner" box="[905,1197,1277,1303]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" refString="Banner, A. H. &amp; Banner, D. M. (1960) Contributions to the knowledge of the alpheid shrimp of the Pacific Ocean, part VII: On Metabetaeus Borradaile, with a new species from Hawaii. Pacific Science, 15, 299 - 303." type="journal article" year="1960">
Banner &amp; Banner (
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFBD5A5DEFB03FA9E" box="[1127,1188,1277,1303]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1960.0">1960</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
did not mention nor illustrate these spine-like setae in 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFD94A400FD39FAB5" box="[550,670,1315,1340]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lohena">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFD94A400FD39FAB5" box="[550,670,1315,1340]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">M. lohena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in the currently examined specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFB4DA400FA32FAB5" box="[1279,1429,1315,1340]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFB4DA400FA32FAB5" box="[1279,1429,1315,1340]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Metabetaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFEA7A46BFE33FAE8" box="[277,404,1352,1377]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lohena">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFEA7A46BFE33FAE8" box="[277,404,1352,1377]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">M. lohena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the P 
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFE55A46BFE52FAEB" box="[487,501,1352,1378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="3.0">3</number>
and P 
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFDF7A46BFDF3FAEB" box="[581,596,1352,1378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="4.0">4</number>
merus is furnished with one to three, sometimes very conspicuous spiniform seta(e), on the ventrolateral surface. Another apparently variable character is the presence or absence of an arthrobranch at the base of the third maxilliped. This gill structure is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFAA1A4B0FA3BFA25" box="[1299,1436,1427,1452]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFAA1A4B0FA3BFA25" box="[1299,1436,1427,1452]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">M. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation id="95444B44FFC2622DFE9CA49BFE4CFA5B" author="Coutiere" box="[302,491,1464,1490]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" refString="Coutiere, H. (1899) Sur le genre Metabetaeus Borradaile. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1899, 19, 374 - 377." type="journal article" year="1899">
Coutière (
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFE11A49BFE45FA5B" box="[419,482,1464,1490]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1899.0">1899</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, which is confirmed by examination of three specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFB2BA49BFABBFA58" box="[1177,1308,1464,1489]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFB2BA49BFABBFA58" box="[1177,1308,1464,1489]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">M. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, a rudimentary arthrobranch appears to be present in the new species (see below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F16A36B5FFC2622DFF74A721FE75F8E5" blockId="2.[151,1437,1240,1900]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFF74A721FE7EF995" bold="true" box="[198,473,1538,1564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Phylogenetic remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFE59A720FD26F995" box="[491,641,1539,1564]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFE59A720FD26F995" box="[491,641,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Metabetaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to have no obvious affinities to any other alpheid genus. 
<bibRefCitation id="95444B44FFC2622DFF25A70BFECCF9CB" author="Borradaile" box="[151,363,1576,1602]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" refString="Borradaile, L. A. (1899) On the Stomatopoda and Macrura brought by Dr. Willey from the South Seas. In: Willey, A. (ed.), Zoological results based on material from New Britain, New Guinea, Loyalty Islands and elsewhere collected during the years 1895, 1896, 1897. Part IV., 20: 395 - 428, pls. 36 - 39. Cambridge." type="journal article" year="1899">
Borradaile (
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFE97A70BFEC4F9CB" box="[293,355,1576,1602]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1899.0">1899</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFD97A70BFD1BF9C8" box="[549,700,1576,1601]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFD97A70BFD1BF9C8" box="[549,700,1576,1601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Metabetaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFC4AA70BFA96F9CB" authority="Holthuis, 1955" authorityName="Holthuis" authorityYear="1955" box="[1016,1329,1576,1602]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Salmoneus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFC4AA70BFBDFF9C8" box="[1016,1144,1576,1601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Salmoneus</emphasis>
Holthuis, 
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFB44A70BFA96F9CB" box="[1270,1329,1576,1602]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1955.0">1955</number>
</taxonomicName>
and also briefly contrasted it with 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFE79A76EFCA8F9EE" authority="Coutiere, 1896" authorityName="Coutiere" authorityYear="1896" box="[459,783,1613,1639]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFE79A76EFDE8F9EF" box="[459,591,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Alpheopsis</emphasis>
Coutière, 
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFD7DA76EFCA8F9EE" box="[719,783,1613,1639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1896.0">1896</number>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="95444B44FFC2622DFCA9A76EFC7BF9EE" author="Coutiere" box="[795,988,1613,1639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" refString="Coutiere, H. (1899) Sur le genre Metabetaeus Borradaile. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1899, 19, 374 - 377." type="journal article" year="1899">
Coutière (
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFC26A76EFC74F9EE" box="[916,979,1613,1639]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1899.0">1899</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that the closest relative of 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFF25A750FE93F905" box="[151,308,1651,1676]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFF25A750FE93F905" box="[151,308,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Metabetaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFE1DA750FCCCF905" authority="Coutiere, 1896" authorityName="Coutiere" authorityYear="1896" box="[431,875,1650,1676]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequalis">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFE1DA750FD01F905" box="[431,678,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Alpheopsis aequalis</emphasis>
Coutière, 
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFC99A751FCCCF905" box="[811,875,1650,1676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1896.0">1896</number>
</taxonomicName>
, because of general similarities in the frontal margin (except for the orbital teeth) and chelipeds. In the phylogenetic analysis of Anker et al. (
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFAF9A7BBFA28F93B" box="[1355,1423,1688,1714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="2006.0">2006</number>
), 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFF25A79EFE88F95F" box="[151,303,1725,1750]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFF25A79EFE88F95F" box="[151,303,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Metabetaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recovered in a weakly supported larger clade that contained several other alpheid genera, including 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFEA2A7C0FE36F975" box="[272,401,1763,1788]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Salmoneus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFEA2A7C0FE36F975" box="[272,401,1763,1788]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Salmoneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(clade 
<collectionCode id="97C4AE70FFC2622DFE58A7C1FDB3F975" box="[490,532,1762,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">SD</collectionCode>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFDEFA7C0FCFCF975" authority="Leach, 1814" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[605,859,1762,1788]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Athanas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFDEFA7C0FD18F975" box="[605,703,1763,1788]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Athanas</emphasis>
Leach, 
<number id="471D2492FFC2622DFCADA7C1FCFCF975" box="[799,859,1762,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" value="1814.0">1814</number>
</taxonomicName>
+ closely related “athanoid” genera (clade 
<collectionCode id="97C4AE70FFC2622DFAD6A7C1FA28F975" box="[1380,1423,1762,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">AP</collectionCode>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFEA9A62BFE19F8A8" box="[283,446,1800,1825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Metabetaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFEA9A62BFE19F8A8" box="[283,446,1800,1825]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Metabetaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not share any exclusive synapomorphies with 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFBD0A62BFB6CF8A8" box="[1122,1227,1800,1825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Athanas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFBD0A62BFB6CF8A8" box="[1122,1227,1800,1825]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Athanas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFB6EA62BFAC1F8A8" box="[1244,1382,1800,1825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Salmoneus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFB6EA62BFAC1F8A8" box="[1244,1382,1800,1825]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Salmoneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFF25A60EFEBDF8CF" box="[151,282,1837,1862]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C3A1EAA7FFC2622DFF25A60EFEBDF8CF" box="[151,282,1837,1862]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="39">Alpheopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, its position within the 
<taxonomicName id="36D54D36FFC2622DFD0CA60EFC9FF8CE" box="[702,824,1837,1863]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Alpheidae</taxonomicName>
remains unclear; it may well represent a relatively distinct lineage on its own.
</paragraph>
